    import os
    import netifaces

    # Find out what the IP addresses are at run time
    # This is necessary because otherwise Gunicorn will reject the connections
    def ip_addresses():
        ip_list = []
        for interface in netifaces.interfaces():
            addrs = netifaces.ifaddresses(interface)
            for x in (netifaces.AF_INET, netifaces.AF_INET6):
                if x in addrs:
                    ip_list.append(addrs[x][0]['addr'])
        return ip_list

    # Discover our IP address

        'seamansguide.com',
        'shrinking-world.com',
        'spiritual-things.org',
        'shrinking-world.com',
    ]

fields.expected:
your company really wants is for you to be in control . Your family and friends do too . They may not have said those words to you , but they want you to be healthy , happy , productive , and engaged in your life . Sounds wonderful , right ? Achieving those glorious goals requires taking control , because control is a main driver in activating the full potential of your brain and changing your behavior . Amazingly , small changes slight alterations in the choices we make can have a dramatic effect on our sense of control . Over time , those small choices build into more dramatic shifts , and then suddenly , you cant believe how different your life is .

we learn helplessness when we believe that we have no options . 4 We give up and nearly shut down . We become victims . On the flipside , those who believe they have options who are optimistic fare better in the world in everything from relationships and careers to health and longevity . Seeing and making choices even if the choice is not to choose is one of the elixirs of life . 5 Making a choice is the signal to our brain that we are ready to begin a journey , which means choice is the first step in all change .

The choices we make affect all of who we are , not just our work . Youll learn in the following chapters that who you are in your career is not separate from who you are in the rest of your life ; work is just another facet of the same diamond . The choices we make at work will affect the choices we make at home , and vice versa .

Start small , start now . You just have to begin even if you really , really , really , really dont want to . The simplest and most crucial step we can all take in living the life we want is to start doing it now . If we wait to have all of our ducks in order , the first ducks we collected will have flown the coop by the time we get to the last ducks and it becomes a never - ending amassing of ducks . The prize goes to those who can get over being completely prepared before they begin .

Accomplishment sets up a chain of pleasure chemistry , while the lack of it does quite the opposite . To leverage the power of our pleasure chemistry , we need to activate .

Most of us have this general low - level anxiety driven by all of those things left undone . But once we activate and start going , were better able to keep on going . A body in motion stays in motion . And it works because our brain rewards us for completing tasks , even just the first step .

our amygdalae are facilitating a shift in our attention to things that are important to both our well - being and our survival . 2 The mammalian brain has been described as the emotional center of the brain : It is not logical and , left to its own devices , it would cause us to act like an undisciplined three - year - old . Fortunately , if conditions are right , the mammalian brain has an overseer the third brain .

Many people make it into great schools and get excellent jobs because theyre technically smart and have high IQs , but they often derail because they never learn to help their human brain manage the mammalian brain . Eventually , the mammalian brain can destroy careers and relationships if we do not recognize how to bring the human brain online when were feeling strongly about something , especially in times of crisis .

Emotional intelligence ( EI ) is the dance between the more rational C system and the emotional X system . EI is a set of noncognitive ( i.e . , non - IQ ) attributes , and if we have high EI , our C system is effectively cooperating with and regulating the X system . EI allows individuals to navigate the day - to - day difficulties and obstacles of life , manage their own emotions , and bring about appropriate emotions in others , all in an effort to be successful . In fact , its a better predictor of individual workplace success and well - being in life than IQ and expertise .

Some scientists8 , 9 estimate that we spend only about 2 to 10 percent of our waking hours in the C system and the rest in the X system which means that most of our time is spent on the animal side of nature , reacting , responding out of impulse , defaulting to the negative , and missing the positive . Thats somewhat understandable : the C system is much more energy intensive to operate , while instantaneous X system reactions are less expensive to operate . In short , most of us have to work to improve our emotional intelligence . We have to decide to spend the energy .

Adrenaline is our fight , flight , or freeze hormone . High levels of it put us in a high arousal state ; low levels or a lack of it put us in a low arousal state . When we perceive a threat , our adrenaline shoots up to put us into high alert , and glucose spills into our bloodstream to give us energy . Being in high arousal can lead to intense feelings , both positive and negative .

Dopamine is our reward transmitter ; 6 it causes pleasant feelings and a sense that we want to do something again . Its required for learning and for building neural pathways , the building blocks of behaviors . When we refer to a dopamine bump , were talking about the feeling we get from a rewarding behavior . Dopamine is essential in motor regulation , too .

Norepinephrine can lead to feelings of alertness , engagement , and reward . It increases during exercise and laughter . It gets your heart pounding to increase blood flow to survive a threat , and it sparks interest and intensity . Oxytocin is a brain - based hormone that is implicated in trust , bonding , and collaborative feelings .

Quadrant II is the most sustainable of the quadrants , and its the source of happiness for most of us in our lives . The feelings in this quadrant include amazement , contentment , serenity , admiration , and trust .

Oxytocin : Bonding Laughter Love / liking / trust Collaboration Generosity Norepinephrine : Focus and excitement Engagement Interest Novelty Dopamine : Completion Goal achievement Mastery Winning

Achieving those glorious goals requires taking control , because control is a main driver in activating the full potential of your brain and changing your behavior . Amazingly , small changes slight alterations in the choices we make can have a dramatic effect on our sense of control . Over time , those small choices build into more dramatic shifts , and then suddenly , you cant believe how different your life is .

we learn helplessness when we believe that we have no options . 4 We give up and nearly shut down . We become victims . The choices we make at work will affect the choices we make at home , and vice versa .

Start small , start now . You just have to begin even if you really , really , really , really dont want to . In fact , its a better predictor of individual workplace success and well - being in life than IQ and expertise .

Who2Hire Partners with ShareAble for Hires from TransUnion

We are happy to announce a Co-Branding relationship between Who2Hire and TransUnions new pre-employment background check service, ShareAble for Hires.

In the tech industry, we are always looking for the next disruptive force thats going to change how things are done in an entire business segment. Designed to especially benefit small businesses, ShareAble for Hires is a game-changer because it provides decision-makers with immediate access to a reliable screening tool with credit and criminal reports designed to comply with the FCRA.  Instead of waiting days for results, now employers can learn critical information in minutes.  We think ShareAble for Hires will change how pre-employment background checks are done because it turns a slow, complicated process into a fast, simple and inexpensive task. Who wouldnt want that?

Who2Hire helps you identify the best person for your job opening. ShareAble for Hires clarifies that decision even more!

#preemployment #backgroundchecks #humanresourses #shareablehires #who2hire #disruptive #bettertogether

https://hires.shareable.com/who2hire

Identify the Best

Who2Hire helps you identify the best person for your job opening.

Research shows that most hires are made based upon gut feeling and whether the interviewers like the person and feel comfortable with them. The success rate of a traditional interview process is about 50% basically a coin toss! Who2Hire utilizes best practice behavioral interviewing techniques to dramatically increase the successful hire rate by as much as 9x.

Competition for the best employees is heating up. The economy and demographics are creating a perfect storm when it comes to hiring. The rate of job creation is increasing, unemployment is falling, and the Baby Boom is retiring by the tens of thousands daily. An investment in improving your successful hire rate will pay deep dividends.

Steve Jobs gave this great advice hiring the best is your most important task.

Can You Afford Another Bad hire?

Replacement cost for a bad hire is 20% to 200% of the annual salary. Highly skilled and management jobs easily cost 200% of the annual salary, or more, to replace.
A bad hire also causes:

  • Lost productivity understaffed
  • Training lost investment
  • Lower employee morale
  • Loss of management/owner credibility inside company
  • Poor community reputation

When you are a busy manager or business owner its easy to just go with what youve been doing and hope for the best. But when you count the cost of hiring the wrong person its obvious that investing in better hiring process is a smart move.

Past Behavior Predicts Future Performance

Memorize this phrase. The best insight into a candidates future performance is gained by understanding their past behavior. By asking questions that invite them to tell you stories about how theyve handled situations in the past you get a glimpse into how they would behave on your team. Avoid asking questions that invite the candidate to tell you what they think or feel about a subject its too easy for some candidates to guess the answer you are looking for without it having any relevance to their job performance.

Who2Hire not only focuses the interview questions toward behavioral content, it also streamlines the hiring process by organizing job openings, candidates, interview teams, and producing a summary report. A library of behavioral aptitudes and interview questions allows companies to gain the benefits of behavioral interviewing techniques without having an in-house HR department. This makes it an ideal tool for startups.

Pricing

Pay as You Go

You pay for one job opening at a time with no set up or monthly fees. Who2Hire is ideally priced for small to medium size businesses only $295 for each new job opening. Simple.

Create a free account now! Sign up

 

Or Own It!

Corporate licensing and white labeling, purchase for HR Consultants or PEO is available. Email info@who2hire.us for more information.

fields.expected_html:
Shrinking World

Seaman Tech

Shrinking World Solutions

Life is short, so live today!

Do not allow your dreams to be neglected. Use them to motivate you into action.

Simple steps you can take today:

  • Capture all of your dreams in writing
  • Prioritize the most important dreams to work on
  • Build a simple plan to act
  • Put tracking in place to keep you going
  • Use milestones as confirmation and renewed energy

Turn Dreams to Reality

Create a roadmap for the journey. Use each success as a spring-board for more progress. Get expert advice from others that have accomplished similar goals.

Aspire lets you instantly see your current commitments and the progress that you are making on them. An automated guide gives you advise about what you should work on next. Integrated tools track your invested time on each project.

Signup for Free

Get started in a few minutes. Basic service is always free. Advanced features are available for $10/month.

Signup

Copyright 2018 Shrinking World

Mark Seaman

Inventor, Author, Geek

  • Advisor - Oracle of Shrinking World
  • ToDo - Next Steps
  • Goals - 1000 Goals
  • Time - Invested Time

Inventor

  • personally written a million lines of code on over 80 software projects

  • pioneer of agile practices and new technologies

  • founder of Shrinking World Solutions an engineering and training company

  • 37 years of professional software development

Author

Books

  • The Leverage Principle

Blogs

  • Seamans Log

  • Shrinking World

  • Working with Shrinking World

Web Services

  • My Book Online

  • Exterior Brain - knowledge management

  • Aspire - goal management

Work Experience

Expertise

Mark uses the best practices of software development to build high-quality software rapidly.

He is a pioneer in software testing and automation techniques.

Mark has experience developing products in a variety of software domains from control systems to digital imaging and Optical Character Recognition.

He has been granted 12 U.S. patents.

Contribution

Mark enjoys creating simple solutions to complex technical problems.

He also enjoys mentoring others in the craft of software engineering.

Contact Info

fields.body:
This wiki documents the development of the reusable software platform, called Hammer.  A large number of design patterns are used to produce a complete standalone wiki tool.  This tool is then extended into a large variety of applications.

This wiki documents the development of the reusable software platform, called Hammer. A large number of design patterns are used to produce a complete standalone wiki tool. This tool is then extended into a large variety of applications.

**Project Requirements**

* Select goals for project
* Create a project plan
* Choose milestones
* Build forms input
* Create view styles
* Document the process and schedule
* Inventory of technical tricks

**Project Milestones**

* **Project Plan** - preparation and design

    * Documented project plan
    * Documented design patterns
    * Web views for issue tracking
    * Web views for project tracking

* **Core Features** - prototype

    * Web hosting
    * Page layout (menu, CSS, style)
    * List all pages
    * Add a new page
    * Edit the title and body text of a page
    * Link pages (eg. /wiki/detail/11)

* **Minimum Viable Product** - engage with others

    * Display text using a slug in the URL
    * Delete a page
    * Page navigation menu


* **Extended Features** - most critical enhancements

    * Export pages to Markdown file directory
    * Import pages from Markdown file directory
    * Automatic page tests using Selenium
    * Automatic tests looking for unexpected results
    * Approval workflow for accepting test results
